{{Infobox building |name = Hilton Garden Inn |image = HiltonCLE.jpg |image_size = 250px |former_names = None |location = 1100 Carnegie Avenue [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]] 44115 United States |building_type = Hotel |floor_count = 11 |start_date = 2000 |completion_date = 2002 |roof = {{convert|36.57 |m|ft|0|abbr=on}} |rooms = 240 |architect = City Architecture }} The '''Hilton Garden Inn''' is a 120-foot 11 story [[high-rise]] hotel in the [[downtown Cleveland]] [[Gateway Sports and Entertainment Complex|Gateway District]].<ref>http://www.emporis.com/buildings/157122/hilton-garden-inn-cleveland-gateway-cleveland-oh-usa ''Hilton Garden Inn Cleveland Gateway'' Retrieved on 2105-09-22</ref> It is [[postmodern architecture|postmodern]] in style and has a color scheme of light red and beige. The Hilton is very squat in structure and occupies over a city block of space length wise, however, width wise it is very thin. It is connected to the Gateway Conference Center. The hotel features 240 rooms and sits directly across the street from [[Progressive Field]] which is the home of the [[Cleveland Indians]].<ref>http://hiltongardeninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/ohio/hilton-garden-inn-cleveland-downtown-CLEGWGI/index.html ''Hilton Garden Inn Cleveland Downtown'' Retrieved on 2015-09-22</ref> It opened in 2002.<ref>http://skyscraperpage.com/cities/?buildingID=21384 ''Hilton Garden Inn Cleveland Gateway'' Retrieved on 2015-09-22</ref> It was one of the first major new hotels constructed in the central city area of downtown in the new millennium. It is one of five Hilton hotels in Cleveland, the other four being the [[Hilton Cleveland Downtown Hotel]] and the [[Double Tree Hotel Cleveland]], [[Hampton Inn (Cleveland)]] and [[Reserve Square]].
The hotel's location on Carnegie Avenue affords it a view of downtown and surrounding areas. Its location adjacent to offramps to Interstates [[Interstate 71|71]], [[Interstate 77|77]], and [[Interstate 90|90]] makes it the city's only downtown hotel near a major highway. This may change, if the [[NuCLEus]] project is completed by 2018.
