'''L. Frank & Son Building''' is a historic [[retail]] building located at [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]], [[United States]]. It  is a four-story brick commercial building with a [[cast iron architecture|cast-iron façade]], built about 1875.  It was constructed for Samuel Stein & Bros.,  and occupied by a dealer in iron ranges and furnaces, and later a series of shoe and clothing manufacturers.<ref name="mht_ihp">{{cite web|url=https://mht.maryland.gov/secure/medusa/PDF/NR_PDFs/NR-1139.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: L. Frank & Son Building|date=May 1990|accessdate=2016-03-01 |author=Peter E. Kurtze|publisher=Maryland Historical Trust}}</ref>

L. Frank & Son Building was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1994.<ref name="nris"/> 
The [[building at 409 West Baltimore Street]], next door, was listed at the same time.

