{{Infobox person | name = Tonyi Senayah | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year with {{Birth year and age|YYYY}} unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]]. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Ghana]]ian | other_names = | occupation = Businessman | education = [[Prempeh College]], [[University of Ghana]] | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Tonyi Senayah''' is a [[Ghana]]ian businessman and the Chief Executive Officer of Horseman Shoes. Senayah began studying shoe making in 2009 under a local shoe maker at [[Lapaz (Accra)|Lapaz]]. The brand has been featured in local and international media, notably ''[[CNN]]'' and DW networks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2014/04/01/horseman-shoes-to-open-retail-outlet/|title=Horseman Shoes to open retail outlet|last=Boateng|first=Kojo Akoto|date=2014-04-01|website=Ghana News|access-date=2017-08-16}}</ref>
== Early life and education ==
Senayah went to [[Prempeh College|Prempeh college]] in [[Kumasi]] and is a sociology graduate of the [[University of Ghana|University of Ghana, Legon]] where he was also a student leader.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.dw.com/en/tonyi-senayahs-story/a-17412785|title=Tonyi Senayah′s story {{!}} Africa {{!}} DW {{!}} 07.02.2014|last=(www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche Welle|website=DW.COM|language=en|access-date=2017-08-17}}</ref>
In 2010, he opened Horseman Shoes, a Ghanaian-based footwear manufacturing company that produces men’s dress shoes, unisex sandals and slippers, school sandals, and safety boots.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/business/Tonyi-Senayah-Is-Young-Entrepreneur-Of-The-Year-2011-226383|title=Tonyi Senayah Is Young Entrepreneur Of The Year 2011|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-03}}</ref>
In 2015, Senayah ranked 9th as the Most Influential Young Ghanaian out of a list of 50 personalities<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newsghana.com.gh/tonyi-senayah-voted-ghanas-most-influential-young-entrepreneur/|title=Tonyi Senayah Voted Ghana’s Most Influential Young Entrepreneur {{!}} News Ghana|date=2016-01-18|work=News Ghana|access-date=2017-08-16|language=en-US}}</ref> and 16th in 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/local/social/201701/302907.php|title=LIST: Fifty (50) Most Influential Young Ghanaian|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2017-08-16}}</ref>
